San Diego Padres' Alex Torres has became the first baseball player to wear a new cap designed to protect pitchers from line drives to the head.

Major League Baseball approved the bulky hat in January, nearly a year-and-a-half after pitcher Brandon McCarthy suffered life-threatening brain injuries when he was struck. He has recovered.

Torres said he copped some flak from team mates when he debuted the oversized cap while pitchingÂ against the Dodgers on Saturday, but insisted it was worth it.

'It could save our lives, if someone hits a ball to your head,' the 26-year-old Venezuelan told MLB.com. 'I get it for free, so I'm just gonna use it to see how it feels.'

